Citation.sTitle: Excess volumes of mixing in (N,N-dimethylacetamide + methanol + water) and (N,N-dimethylacetamide + ethanol + water) at the temperature 313.15 K
Citation.sAbstract: Precise excess volumes of mixing measurements at T = 313.15 K are reported over the whole composition range for binary mixtures: (N,N-dimethylacetamide + water), (N,N-dimethyl-acetamide + methanol), (N,N-dimethylacetamide + ethanol) and for the ternary mixtures (N,N-dimethylacetamide + methanol + water) and (N,N-dimethylacetamide + ethanol + water). For all the systems, large negative deviations from ideality are observed. The binary results have been fitted using the Redlich Kister type polynomial. The possibility of predicting the ternary results from the binary ones was examined.
